  "response_text": "# Gluten-Free Meal Plan\n\n## Breakfast Options\n- Eggs (scrambled, omelet, or fried) with vegetables\n- Oatmeal (certified gluten-free) with fruit and nuts\n- Greek yogurt with berries and granola (gluten-free)\n- Smoothie bowls with fruit and coconut\n- Gluten-free toast with avocado or nut butter\n\n## Lunch Ideas\n- Grilled chicken with roasted vegetables and rice\n- Salad with protein (tuna, chickpeas, or grilled tofu)\n- Rice bowls with beans, vegetables, and avocado\n- Lettuce wraps with ground turkey and vegetables\n- Corn tortilla tacos with beans and salsa\n\n## Dinner Suggestions\n- Baked salmon with sweet potato and broccoli\n- Ground beef with zucchini noodles and marinara\n- Grilled steak with quinoa and asparagus\n- Chicken stir-fry with rice\n- Pork chops with mashed potatoes and green beans\n\n## Snacks\n- Fresh fruit and nuts\n- Cheese and crackers (gluten-free)\n- Hummus with vegetables\n- Hard-boiled eggs\n- Popcorn\n\n## Key Tips\n- Read labels carefully (many processed foods contain hidden gluten)\n- Use naturally gluten-free grains: rice, quinoa, corn, potatoes\n- Avoid wheat, barley, rye, and regular oats\n- Cross-contamination matters—use separate kitchen tools if needed\n\nWould you like specific recipes or a shopping list?",
